WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:05.292
[pages riffling]

00:08.000 --> 00:11.000
♪

00:23.833 --> 00:26.417
♪

00:31.958 --> 00:34.917
[water bubbling]

00:34.917 --> 00:38.958
♪ Madeline Bell's Love is All playing ♪

00:41.125 --> 00:43.083
[hooting]

00:43.083 --> 00:44.292
‐ Oh my god.

00:44.958 --> 00:46.958
[grunting]

00:48.250 --> 00:51.917
♪

00:55.792 --> 00:57.458
[growls]

00:57.458 --> 01:01.042
‐ ♪ Love is all I am needing ♪

01:01.625 --> 01:06.042
♪ Now you are here in my life ♪

01:06.042 --> 01:09.750
♪ And good is all I am feeling ♪

01:10.458 --> 01:14.958
♪ Where have you been
all my life? ♪

01:15.917 --> 01:17.208
[hooting]

01:18.000 --> 01:20.250
[squelching]

01:22.208 --> 01:23.875
[growling]

01:23.875 --> 01:27.750
‐ The war between the Yokahama
and Ozu campaigns continues,

01:27.750 --> 01:31.292
with the Yokahama camp
now openly accusing Counselor Ozu

01:31.292 --> 01:34.375
of being connected
to the assassination of Ken Takahara.

01:34.792 --> 01:35.667
[TV switches off]
‐ Hey.

01:35.667 --> 01:37.083
[Akiko sighs]
I was watching that.

01:37.083 --> 01:39.833
‐ You know, I can't remember
the last day I had off.

01:39.833 --> 01:40.583
[hoots]

01:40.583 --> 01:41.917
‐ Jesus.

01:42.250 --> 01:45.333
How'd we go from killing people
to being in a yogurt commercial?

01:45.333 --> 01:47.083
It's gross seeing you
get this soft.

01:47.083 --> 01:48.833
[growls, grunts]

01:48.833 --> 01:50.583
AKIKO: Now let's make sure
you don't get dirty!

01:50.583 --> 01:52.333
[whimpers, hoots]

01:52.750 --> 01:54.000
[snarls]

01:54.000 --> 01:54.917
‐ Exactly.

01:54.917 --> 01:56.833
[knocking on door,
doorbell rings continuously]

01:56.833 --> 01:57.417
[grunts]

01:57.417 --> 01:58.958
‐ Who the hell is this?

01:59.792 --> 02:00.750
[hooting]

02:04.417 --> 02:05.708
‐ We need to talk.

02:06.417 --> 02:09.042
♪ dramatic theme playing ♪

02:09.042 --> 02:12.292
♪

02:19.083 --> 02:20.917
[coughs]

02:20.917 --> 02:22.083
[clears throat]

02:24.250 --> 02:25.250
[sighs]

02:25.250 --> 02:26.958
Sorry to show up uninvited,

02:26.958 --> 02:29.250
but your uncle's a tough man
to schedule time with.

02:29.958 --> 02:31.667
I tried to give you a call,

02:32.500 --> 02:35.708
but we've apprehended the prime suspect
in Ken Takahara's murder.

02:35.708 --> 02:38.125
‐ Wait, you've arrested
Counselor Ozu?

02:38.125 --> 02:39.917
‐ What? Ozu?

02:40.292 --> 02:41.292
N‐no.

02:41.292 --> 02:44.208
He's a Yakuza boss
who goes by the name "The Rooster."

02:44.792 --> 02:47.708
He's the only person with direct ties
to every other suspect.

02:47.708 --> 02:49.750
‐ Hey! He's talking
about our guy!

02:49.750 --> 02:52.167
‐ We booked him, but we have
no way to hold him.

02:52.167 --> 02:53.667
‐ What do you mean
you can't hold him?

02:53.667 --> 02:55.292
‐ Because he's connected.

02:55.292 --> 02:56.708
No judge is gonna
take the case.

02:56.708 --> 02:59.417
No prosecutor is going
to risk their career going after him.

02:59.750 --> 03:02.417
The Rooster has blackmail
on every politician in Tokyo.

03:02.417 --> 03:04.833
HARUKA: We can't even
hold him for 24 hours.

03:04.833 --> 03:06.458
They're releasing him
this morning.

03:06.458 --> 03:08.917
‐ This morning?
This is outrageous.

03:08.917 --> 03:12.125
‐ Amazing what a few hundred
well‐placed Polaroids can do for you.

03:12.542 --> 03:15.750
‐ So that's it? You got the guy,
but he can't be prosecuted?

03:15.750 --> 03:17.083
How convenient.

03:17.083 --> 03:19.750
Has anybody even looked
into whether he's connected to Ozu?

03:19.750 --> 03:22.375
I wouldn't put it past him
to hire Yakuza to do his dirty work.

03:22.375 --> 03:24.250
‐ I'm sorry, Miss Yokohama,

03:24.250 --> 03:26.667
but there's no evidence
to prove that.

03:26.667 --> 03:28.000
‐ According to who?

03:28.000 --> 03:30.292
‐ Well, uh,
according to our sources

03:31.042 --> 03:32.542
and police work.

03:32.542 --> 03:34.000
[chuckles derisively]

03:34.000 --> 03:35.583
‐ Guess that's‐that's
a joke, right?

03:35.583 --> 03:36.042
[clears throat]

03:36.042 --> 03:39.417
‐ The bottom line is that
we're just as frustrated as you are.

03:39.417 --> 03:40.583
‐ They're releasing him?

03:40.583 --> 03:42.375
‐ Oh, bud,
this could be good for us!

03:42.375 --> 03:43.792
[meows]

03:43.792 --> 03:45.000
Hey! Get out of here, cat!

03:45.000 --> 03:46.917
Shoo! Shoo! Scram!

03:46.917 --> 03:48.375
‐ Well, that explains
my allergies.

03:48.375 --> 03:50.167
‐ Bradley! Come on.
Get away from there!

03:50.167 --> 03:51.917
‐ Aww, what a sweet cat.

03:52.250 --> 03:54.417
I wasn't able to bring mine
when I moved to Tokyo.

03:54.417 --> 03:55.708
‐ Uh, he doesn't like
getting picked up!

03:56.667 --> 03:58.708
‐ Oh, uh, okay.

03:58.708 --> 03:59.792
AKIKO:
Sor‐‐ I'm sorry, I'm‐‐

04:00.458 --> 04:01.625
but I'm gonna have
to ask you to leave.

04:02.000 --> 04:03.792
I have a very busy day
and I just‐‐

04:05.167 --> 04:06.000
Okay?

04:07.417 --> 04:09.333
‐ Absolutely, Miss Yokohama.
‐ What?

04:09.333 --> 04:10.792
‐ We realize
the stress you're under

04:10.792 --> 04:12.708
and want to let you know
the Tokyo PD

04:13.250 --> 04:14.125
[clears throat]

04:14.125 --> 04:16.333
is doing the best it can.

04:18.083 --> 04:21.375
‐ You know, it's a shame
the police have become so ineffective.

04:21.375 --> 04:24.042
You almost wish there was somebody
who could clean things up in this town.

04:24.750 --> 04:26.542
‐ Have a nice day, ma'am.

04:36.833 --> 04:37.875
‐ Monkey?

04:42.667 --> 04:44.708
HARUKA:
She's hiding something. I know it.

04:44.708 --> 04:46.458
‐ She's a politician.

04:46.458 --> 04:48.125
They're all hiding something.

04:48.417 --> 04:51.500
You're just jealous of her house
and that fat‐ass cat.

04:51.500 --> 04:52.708
‐ That's a cute cat.

04:52.708 --> 04:54.458
And Akiko is
an entitled princess

04:54.458 --> 04:56.708
pretending to be
some champion of the people.

04:57.042 --> 04:58.875
And you let her just
push us around.

04:58.875 --> 05:01.792
‐ Haruka, you don't want
her kind of trouble. Trust me.

05:02.417 --> 05:05.250
Come on. You really think
she's connected to The Rooster?

05:05.250 --> 05:06.125
To all of this?

05:08.542 --> 05:10.292
BRYCE: I'm sorry, how could you
be confused by this?

05:10.292 --> 05:12.667
It's like criminal chain
of command 101.

05:12.667 --> 05:14.000
The Rooster hired
the Accountant,

05:14.000 --> 05:15.625
who paid the Old Fish Lady,

05:15.625 --> 05:18.167
who got her tacky‐ass twins
to leverage the army guy to,

05:18.167 --> 05:20.250
and‐and this is the important part
that I really want to,

05:20.250 --> 05:21.625
you know,
just make sure you hear:

05:21.625 --> 05:24.292
Send a bunch of assholes
to kill me.

05:24.708 --> 05:25.417
[ooks]

05:25.417 --> 05:27.500
Yeah, no, and kill
your entire family too.

05:27.500 --> 05:28.250
[ooks]

05:28.250 --> 05:30.583
So why don't we stop tanning
our assholes up here

05:30.583 --> 05:32.333
and go kill the only guy
on this chart

05:32.333 --> 05:33.208
who isn't already dead.

05:33.208 --> 05:35.000
[grunts, ooks]

05:35.458 --> 05:37.750
Uh... right, no. As soon as
the cops let him go.

05:38.125 --> 05:39.208
Then we'll kill him.

05:46.792 --> 05:48.667
[Monkey whimpers, ooks]

05:48.667 --> 05:50.833
BRYCE: Okay, so we've been following
The Rooster for weeks now,

05:50.833 --> 05:51.917
and we know
he's the top, right?

05:51.917 --> 05:53.083
That cop just confirmed it.

05:53.500 --> 05:56.125
And the priest said
once we kill the top of the chain,

05:56.125 --> 05:57.667
then I ascend.

05:57.667 --> 06:01.167
Or evolve. Or, uh, turn into a big ball
of light or some shit.

06:01.167 --> 06:02.583
I don't know, whatever.
[Monkey grunts]

06:02.583 --> 06:04.833
Look, anyway,
what I'm trying to say is,

06:04.833 --> 06:06.833
I‐I think this might be
my last day on Earth.

06:06.833 --> 06:07.667
[ooks]

06:07.667 --> 06:09.708
Ooh. You know, I gotta admit,

06:10.417 --> 06:11.875
I might actually miss this.

06:13.375 --> 06:15.792
And yeah, at first I‐‐
well, I definitely hated you.

06:15.792 --> 06:17.333
[grunts]
Well, I mean, I don't even like dogs,

06:17.333 --> 06:18.708
so this was
a real challenge.

06:18.708 --> 06:20.292
But, you know what,

06:20.292 --> 06:21.792
it's been a heck
of a ride, man.

06:22.167 --> 06:23.958
I guess what I'm trying
to say is, uh,

06:24.333 --> 06:26.208
I'm happy I met you.
You know?

06:26.208 --> 06:27.042
[chuckles]

06:27.417 --> 06:30.375
Though watching you
around women is truly nauseating.

06:30.375 --> 06:30.917
[Monkey grunts]

06:31.125 --> 06:32.708
I mean, you do not
play it cool, man.

06:32.708 --> 06:34.167
You're as smooth
as sandpaper.

06:34.167 --> 06:35.292
[Monkey ooks]

06:35.292 --> 06:36.833
Oh hell, look at this guy.

06:36.833 --> 06:40.375
He looks like if Roy Orbison had sex
with a bag of salt.

06:40.375 --> 06:41.625
[laughs]

06:41.625 --> 06:43.208
And yeah, no, I know
that's a reference

06:43.208 --> 06:44.292
you'll never appreciate.

06:44.292 --> 06:46.333
But do you understand
how frustrating it is

06:46.333 --> 06:48.417
to waste all this gold
on someone who just learned

06:48.417 --> 06:49.875
what a goddamn fork is?

06:55.917 --> 06:57.917
I'm just saying that
if you plan on hanging out

06:57.917 --> 06:59.875
with other humans
after I'm gone,

06:59.875 --> 07:02.083
some basic knowledge
of pop culture is gonna help.

07:02.083 --> 07:04.167
I mean,
killing people is dope

07:04.167 --> 07:05.750
but so is knowing
who Tom Petty is.

07:05.750 --> 07:06.750
[grunting]

07:06.750 --> 07:07.583
Who's Tom Petty?

07:08.042 --> 07:11.458
I mean, he's like if, uh...
if weed was a person. You know?

07:11.458 --> 07:13.667
Wa‐wait. I forget. Have we
talked about weed yet?

07:14.042 --> 07:15.792
‐ Come on, faster, old man.

07:15.792 --> 07:16.833
I'm in a hurry.

07:17.333 --> 07:18.792
‐ I cannot.

07:19.375 --> 07:23.000
Otherwise,
you might get nicked.

07:23.000 --> 07:24.417
[glass shatters]

07:24.417 --> 07:26.833
‐ Oh, goddammit!
[Monkey shrieks]

07:27.417 --> 07:28.333
[growls]

07:28.333 --> 07:29.958
[punches landing, glass shattering]
BRYCE: Oh wow.

07:29.958 --> 07:32.000
See, now, this is why I always tell them
to use the clippers.

07:32.000 --> 07:33.583
[Monkey shrieking]

07:33.583 --> 07:35.958
‐ Alright. Off I go.

07:35.958 --> 07:37.708
Up, up, and away.

07:38.875 --> 07:40.500
Should be
any minute now.

07:42.250 --> 07:43.667
Uh‐‐

07:45.958 --> 07:48.083
Maybe it takes an hour?
[Monkey ooks]

07:48.083 --> 07:50.042
I‐I mean, logistically
that makes sense, right?

07:50.042 --> 07:52.042
It's a really, really far way
to go, so‐‐

07:52.042 --> 07:53.125
It should take a while.

07:53.125 --> 07:55.042
I‐I think it'd be crazy
actually if it didn't.

07:56.042 --> 07:58.167
You know what, maybe it's like
the DMV up there.

07:58.167 --> 07:59.458
They gotta be backed up.

07:59.458 --> 08:02.958
So. Wait, maybe they give you
this time to reflect and shit.

08:02.958 --> 08:03.792
[grunts]

08:03.792 --> 08:05.542
You know? What if
this is like confession?

08:06.375 --> 08:08.000
What are you look‐‐
Holy shit!

08:08.375 --> 08:10.208
Is that a ghost?
Can he hear me? Can he‐‐

08:10.208 --> 08:11.417
Hello!
[ooks]

08:11.417 --> 08:13.000
That prick had a double!

08:13.000 --> 08:13.708
Of course!

08:13.708 --> 08:15.208
I knew
it was too easy!

08:15.208 --> 08:16.750
This is the guy
we're supposed to kill!

08:16.750 --> 08:17.625
Sneaky shit!

08:18.792 --> 08:19.917
[yelps]

08:19.917 --> 08:22.292
Okay, maybe this time,
go for the head, huh?

08:22.833 --> 08:23.875
[tires squealing]
[people screaming]

08:23.875 --> 08:26.042
Okay, shit. Shit. There's, uh,
so much more to say.

08:26.042 --> 08:28.292
I'll make it quick.
Alright: take care of yourself, man.

08:28.292 --> 08:29.417
Make a good life, okay.

08:31.083 --> 08:32.417
Okay, now take a shot!

08:33.833 --> 08:34.708
There we go.
[tires squealing]

08:36.375 --> 08:37.458
Bullseye!

08:37.875 --> 08:39.375
Dude, you've really gotten
good at this.

08:39.375 --> 08:40.583
[Monkey grunts]
[people screaming]

08:40.583 --> 08:41.542
Ah, shit! What else, what else.

08:41.542 --> 08:45.125
Um, you know, you're gonna wanna
eat your vegetables, say your prayers.

08:45.125 --> 08:47.042
Uh, let's see,
uh, drink more water!

08:47.042 --> 08:48.875
Somebody told me that.
I‐I can't remember who,

08:48.875 --> 08:50.458
it was probably bullshit,
but it might not be.

08:50.750 --> 08:52.292
You know?
It probably can't hurt!

08:52.292 --> 08:54.500
Um. Okay, finish him off.

08:54.500 --> 08:56.583
I am this close
to retirement!

08:57.958 --> 08:59.917
Run! Brothers. Run away!

08:59.917 --> 09:02.625
Run away!
MAN: Oh god!

09:02.625 --> 09:03.917
[groans]

09:04.708 --> 09:05.750
[whimpers]

09:05.750 --> 09:06.833
‐ Nothing's ever simple.

09:06.833 --> 09:08.708
[explosion booms]

09:13.375 --> 09:16.875
‐ When I found out
who was driving that van,

09:16.875 --> 09:21.167
I made sure the person was held
accountable for their actions.

09:21.167 --> 09:24.500
Even though it had nothing
to do with me!

09:24.500 --> 09:28.000
And yet, here we have
my opponent

09:28.000 --> 09:30.417
refusing to fire his niece

09:30.417 --> 09:33.375
after the wild accusations
she made against me.

09:33.375 --> 09:35.375
But what else would you expect

09:35.375 --> 09:38.333
from the same people
who support a cop killer!

09:38.333 --> 09:39.417
‐ I'm turning this garbage off.

09:39.417 --> 09:42.208
‐ I told you something like this
was going to happen.

09:42.208 --> 09:44.000
We've given him ammunition,

09:44.000 --> 09:46.333
of course he's going
to use it against us.

09:46.333 --> 09:49.667
‐ I'm not letting that crook control
the narrative of this campaign!

09:49.667 --> 09:50.667
I got this.

09:51.042 --> 09:52.042
[gunshots]
[Monkey shrieking]

09:52.042 --> 09:54.875
‐ Come on. Monkey, we gotta make sure
we get all of them!

09:55.625 --> 09:58.333
If we miss even one,
I could be here forever.

09:58.333 --> 10:00.125
And‐and I don't think
you want that, do you?

10:00.500 --> 10:01.542
[men screaming]

10:01.542 --> 10:02.917
I mean, just shoot
the slow one at least.

10:02.917 --> 10:05.042
‐ They don't pay us enough
for this crap!

10:05.042 --> 10:05.833
[tires squealing]

10:05.833 --> 10:08.000
‐ Ohh! Ooh!

10:09.292 --> 10:10.167
‐ Oh my god.

10:10.167 --> 10:11.750
[tires squealing]

10:11.750 --> 10:14.292
‐ Okay, alright,
bye for real this time.

10:14.292 --> 10:15.542
And, uh,
say a prayer for me.

10:15.542 --> 10:18.417
I mean, I'm not religious,
but might as well hedge my bets, right?

10:18.750 --> 10:19.917
[sighs]

10:19.917 --> 10:22.000
Should be coming to get me
any second now.

10:24.125 --> 10:25.500
[Monkey groans]

10:27.167 --> 10:27.958
[ooks]

10:27.958 --> 10:28.792
Goddammit!

10:28.792 --> 10:30.625
Did that not count
'cause it wasn't us?

10:31.208 --> 10:33.667
I better not get stuck here
on a technicality.

10:33.667 --> 10:35.708
We probably should've asked
that damn priest more questions

10:35.708 --> 10:37.250
about how
this whole thing works.

10:37.250 --> 10:38.375
Wonder if we can Google it.

10:38.375 --> 10:39.250
[grunts]

10:39.250 --> 10:40.583
‐ Oh god, the monkey!

10:40.583 --> 10:41.625
Run!

10:41.625 --> 10:42.583
‐ Run!

10:43.292 --> 10:44.542
BRYCE: Okay, here we go!

10:44.542 --> 10:46.000
I got a good feeling
about this one.

10:47.500 --> 10:49.875
Never thought I'd be enlightened
in a public bathroom,

10:49.875 --> 10:51.250
but here we are.

10:52.500 --> 10:55.083
Aw, come on, man,
just shoot all the stalls!

10:55.083 --> 10:57.125
You know?
Boom, boom, boom.

10:57.125 --> 10:59.083
Spend the bullets,
save the time, right?

10:59.792 --> 11:01.917
Oh man, I wish
I had more time.

11:01.917 --> 11:03.583
You know,
I used to draw a lot.

11:03.833 --> 11:06.250
It was my passion as a kid.
I was pretty decent, too.

11:06.250 --> 11:08.292
I once drew a bowl of fruit
you could have eaten out of.

11:08.292 --> 11:08.708
[chuckles]

11:08.708 --> 11:11.333
You know, sometimes I wonder
how many people would still be alive

11:11.333 --> 11:13.667
if I'd chosen
to draw fruit instead.

11:13.667 --> 11:14.625
[shrieks]

11:14.625 --> 11:15.750
‐ No, no, no, Monkey.

11:15.750 --> 11:18.083
Wa‐wa‐wait, wait.
I've seen the news.

11:18.083 --> 11:19.875
You only kill killers.

11:19.875 --> 11:21.375
[growls]

11:21.375 --> 11:23.750
I'm no killer.
Look at me.

11:23.750 --> 11:24.708
I'm an actor.

11:25.167 --> 11:26.292
‐ Oh boy, oh boy.

11:26.292 --> 11:27.708
‐ You're looking
for the short one.

11:27.708 --> 11:29.667
The short one is
the real Rooster.

11:29.667 --> 11:31.375
[ooks]

11:31.375 --> 11:32.458
I have children.

11:33.500 --> 11:35.417
Please. Let me go.

11:37.083 --> 11:38.583
[grunts]

11:39.667 --> 11:41.500
[hooting, shrieking]

11:43.167 --> 11:44.750
‐ [panting] Wait.

11:46.458 --> 11:48.083
[growling]
‐ Okay. Here we go.

11:48.083 --> 11:49.333
This has got
to be the last one.

11:49.333 --> 11:50.875
‐ Before you do anything,

11:50.875 --> 11:54.042
know that you'd be making
a big mistake killing me.

11:54.917 --> 11:55.708
You see this?

11:56.292 --> 11:59.750
I have information
on everybody!

11:59.750 --> 12:02.250
The answer you're looking for
is in this box.

12:02.250 --> 12:03.333
[gunshot]
[screams]

12:03.333 --> 12:04.250
‐ What the hell?

12:04.667 --> 12:05.958
Was that you?
[Monkey grunts]

12:05.958 --> 12:07.208
[shrieks]

12:08.417 --> 12:11.417
See! I told you this was
the real dude. They're all after him!

12:11.417 --> 12:13.667
[groaning]

12:13.667 --> 12:16.125
‐ I never said anything,
asshole!

12:16.125 --> 12:18.958
‐ I don't care!
The boss wants you dead!

12:18.958 --> 12:20.792
‐ Shit! Aw, shit, shit, shit!

12:20.792 --> 12:23.000
Don't let them get the kill!
The last bullet wins!

12:23.750 --> 12:26.292
[screams]

12:27.375 --> 12:29.250
Oh, son of a bitch, maybe I need
to confess to ascend.

12:29.250 --> 12:30.750
Uh, okay, what am I leaving out?

12:30.750 --> 12:33.458
Oh, okay! I was in love
with a man once!

12:33.458 --> 12:35.667
[Rooster crying out in pain]
I never told him how I felt!

12:35.667 --> 12:37.417
Not a month goes by
that I don't think of him.

12:37.917 --> 12:39.875
Okay, point is,
never leave things unsaid!

12:39.875 --> 12:40.833
[gunshots continue]

12:40.833 --> 12:41.917
[growling]

12:45.708 --> 12:47.208
You can still see me,
can't you?

12:47.208 --> 12:48.458
[Monkey grunts]
Aw, shit!

12:50.375 --> 12:51.875
What about now?
[ooks]

12:51.875 --> 12:53.875
Like, am I starting
to disappear?

12:53.875 --> 12:55.750
You know, maybe I'm down
at 90 percent?

12:56.250 --> 12:58.000
Shit!

12:58.000 --> 12:59.083
[Monkey ooks]

12:59.083 --> 13:01.167
[Bryce groans]

13:02.083 --> 13:03.083
Alright, let's go.

13:06.375 --> 13:08.792
‐ Well, that's three less scumbags
we have to worry about.

13:09.250 --> 13:11.250
At least this monkey takes out
the bad guys.

13:11.250 --> 13:12.292
I'll give him that.

13:12.292 --> 13:13.292
‐ Jesus.

13:13.292 --> 13:15.667
Leave it to you to blur the lines
between what's right

13:16.125 --> 13:17.333
and what's wrong.

13:17.333 --> 13:20.417
‐ You know, you've been busting
my balls all morning.

13:20.417 --> 13:23.458
If you have something to accuse me of,
just come out and say it.

13:23.458 --> 13:24.417
‐ Okay.

13:24.417 --> 13:27.208
Your idea of police work
and mine are pretty different.

13:27.208 --> 13:28.583
You steal evidence,

13:28.583 --> 13:30.125
you root for a vigilante,

13:30.125 --> 13:32.167
and you still haven't explained
about your past.

13:32.625 --> 13:34.042
If I can't trust my partner,

13:34.042 --> 13:35.083
then I can't do my job.

13:35.792 --> 13:37.125
That's just how I'm built.

13:37.583 --> 13:38.625
‐ You want the truth?

13:39.375 --> 13:40.292
Fine.

13:40.875 --> 13:42.667
Let's finish this up
and go get a coffee.

13:43.875 --> 13:44.792
[shutter clicks]

13:46.625 --> 13:48.125
Haruka, what you
don't understand is that

13:48.125 --> 13:50.000
Tokyo was even more corrupt
back then.

13:50.417 --> 13:52.917
Everybody, I mean everybody,
was on the take.

13:53.208 --> 13:55.083
It was the only way
you could get anything done.

13:55.583 --> 13:58.708
Hell, probably the same now,
but just not so overt.

13:59.167 --> 14:01.833
Anyway, new mayor,
young DA,

14:01.833 --> 14:03.417
they decided
to make an example.

14:03.833 --> 14:05.833
My first partner and I
got caught up in a sting

14:05.833 --> 14:08.458
for doing nothing different
than anyone else.

14:08.458 --> 14:10.042
But they threw
the book at us.

14:10.667 --> 14:13.292
My partner had a young child,
was newly married,

14:13.292 --> 14:15.542
and I was single.

14:15.542 --> 14:17.375
So I took the rap
for both of us.

14:18.083 --> 14:20.833
They gave me suspension.
Demoted me.

14:22.167 --> 14:23.458
Marked my record forever.

14:24.042 --> 14:25.375
‐ What about your partner?

14:25.875 --> 14:28.333
‐ He's doing fine.
‐ But who was it?

14:28.333 --> 14:29.583
‐ It's not important.

14:29.958 --> 14:31.250
He was a shitty partner.

14:31.750 --> 14:32.708
Unlike Hiroshi.

14:34.042 --> 14:35.042
Unlike you.

14:37.042 --> 14:38.833
Masta, another whiskey.

14:40.250 --> 14:42.000
HARUKA:
Make that two whiskeys.

14:47.292 --> 14:50.500
[distant siren wailing]

14:58.292 --> 14:59.250
[grunts]

15:03.417 --> 15:05.542
‐ You feel tired?
Tell me about it.

15:05.542 --> 15:07.833
I'm so raw right now,
I'm a nub.

15:07.833 --> 15:09.125
[grunting]

15:09.125 --> 15:10.625
Now you wanna go
to the bank?

15:10.625 --> 15:12.333
Why?
That's off‐mission.

15:12.333 --> 15:13.625
[hoots]
[chuckles]

15:13.625 --> 15:16.250
That guy was going to say anything
to get you not to shoot him.

15:16.250 --> 15:19.208
"Ooh, Monkey, the secret
to everything is in this box."

15:19.208 --> 15:21.208
[chuckles] What the hell
does that even mean?

15:21.208 --> 15:21.750
[grunts]

15:21.750 --> 15:24.167
Do you have any idea
how emotionally taxing

15:24.167 --> 15:25.375
this day has been for me?

15:25.375 --> 15:28.375
So no, I don't want to go
on your little scavenger hunt, okay.

15:28.375 --> 15:29.542
It's a fool's errand.

15:29.542 --> 15:31.500
Besides, how would we
even get in there?

15:31.500 --> 15:34.083
You killed every double
that could possibly walk us into the‐‐

15:37.125 --> 15:38.167
How far do you think he got?

15:38.167 --> 15:39.125
[grunts]

15:39.708 --> 15:42.167
♪

15:43.375 --> 15:44.417
[slurps]

15:45.042 --> 15:45.875
[Monkey growls]

15:45.875 --> 15:48.917
‐ Oh, come on.
I thought we were good!

15:48.917 --> 15:50.875
‐ Yeah, well,
we lied, dipshit.

15:51.542 --> 15:53.333
‐ Hey! W‐what's this? A key?

15:53.792 --> 15:55.375
I've never seen it before.

15:55.375 --> 15:56.792
[Monkey growling]

15:56.792 --> 15:58.375
‐ This day is never going to end.

15:58.375 --> 15:59.292
[shrieks]

15:59.292 --> 16:00.750
‐ Fine, fine!

16:01.292 --> 16:03.208
Can I at least finish
my noodles?

16:06.583 --> 16:08.417
Play it cool, play it cool.

16:09.208 --> 16:10.917
Security guards are cool.

16:10.917 --> 16:12.458
Everybody's cool.
[Monkey growls]

16:12.458 --> 16:13.458
ROOSTER DOUBLE:
I'm cool.

16:13.458 --> 16:15.958
‐ You know, Monkey, I actually have
something I want to say real quick, okay.

16:15.958 --> 16:18.917
I feel like I've done a lot
of personal growth today,

16:18.917 --> 16:20.500
and you've given me zero.

16:20.500 --> 16:22.500
So I am done
opening up to you.

16:22.500 --> 16:24.208
You're clearly
not mature enough.

16:25.042 --> 16:26.000
Nothing?

16:26.375 --> 16:28.125
You don't have anything
you wanna say to me?

16:28.583 --> 16:30.458
And your silence
has spoken volumes.

16:30.458 --> 16:32.000
I read you loud
and clear, pal.

16:32.000 --> 16:32.958
[whines, grunts]

16:32.958 --> 16:35.458
Okay, fine! Then I guess
we're just doing a bank heist!

16:35.833 --> 16:38.208
God forbid we make
a human connection here.

16:38.917 --> 16:41.417
ROOSTER DOUBLE: I think
that went pretty smoothly! Don't you?

16:41.417 --> 16:43.625
[sneezes]
Whoopsie‐daisy.

16:43.625 --> 16:45.250
[shrieking]

16:45.250 --> 16:47.042
‐ Oh, Jesus.
Look at this guy.

16:47.042 --> 16:49.792
He can't even hold on to the key
with those greasy little sausages

16:49.792 --> 16:50.750
he calls fingers.

16:50.750 --> 16:53.292
[Monkey growls]
‐ I congratulate you, Monkey.

16:53.583 --> 16:56.167
You have managed to accomplish
what the police,

16:56.167 --> 16:59.833
the Yakuza, and all
the most powerful people in Japan

16:59.833 --> 17:01.000
failed to.

17:01.000 --> 17:04.875
Unfortunately, this key
is worthless.

17:04.875 --> 17:05.875
[ooks]

17:05.875 --> 17:10.083
You think I would trust
one of those morons

17:10.083 --> 17:12.458
with something so valuable.

17:12.750 --> 17:13.917
I believe

17:13.917 --> 17:15.833
you're looking
for this one.

17:15.833 --> 17:16.625
‐ Wait.

17:17.125 --> 17:18.583
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
Hold on here!

17:18.583 --> 17:19.708
[grunting]

17:21.833 --> 17:23.875
‐ Did you actually believe

17:23.875 --> 17:27.458
you could outsmart
someone like me?

17:27.458 --> 17:29.000
BRYCE:
Holy shit!

17:29.000 --> 17:31.417
Toilet Rooster is
the real Rooster!

17:31.417 --> 17:33.125
Buddy, you were right
about the box!

17:33.125 --> 17:34.500
I'm really getting
out of here!

17:34.500 --> 17:36.167
ROOSTER:
You stupid animal!

17:36.500 --> 17:37.875
‐ Uh, okay, okay, okay.
This is it.

17:37.875 --> 17:39.667
Oh shit,
uh, my last moments on Earth,

17:39.667 --> 17:40.708
or whatever this is.

17:41.375 --> 17:43.083
There's so much
I need you to do‐‐

17:43.083 --> 17:45.250
Okay, I've got a daughter!
[Monkey grunts]

17:46.208 --> 17:47.167
You've got to find her!

17:47.792 --> 17:49.208
[thudding]
And you gotta make her understand

17:49.208 --> 17:50.042
that I loved her!

17:50.042 --> 17:51.375
Alright?
And‐and‐and,

17:51.375 --> 17:53.542
and don't let her marry someone
like me, 'cause that happens!

17:53.542 --> 17:55.208
And I don't even wanna think
about what kind

17:55.208 --> 17:56.708
of daddy issues she's dealing with! So‐‐

17:56.708 --> 17:57.292
[grunts]

17:57.292 --> 17:59.833
Okay, uh, listen, there's some money
in a bank that I want you to give her!

17:59.833 --> 18:01.292
I‐I‐‐ you gotta hire
a lawyer, too,

18:01.292 --> 18:02.917
'cause I never got around
to doing a will,

18:02.917 --> 18:04.375
so you're going to have
to be the executor.

18:04.375 --> 18:05.500
[shrieking]
[grunts]

18:05.500 --> 18:08.708
I don't... I‐I‐I don't want her
to spend it all when she's 21!

18:08.708 --> 18:09.583
Make her go to college!

18:10.125 --> 18:11.417
[clang]
[groans]

18:12.958 --> 18:14.792
I‐I never had a son.

18:15.458 --> 18:18.208
But if I did, I'd want him
to be just like you!

18:19.083 --> 18:19.958
[hoots]

18:19.958 --> 18:21.500
[Rooster yells]

18:22.250 --> 18:23.042
[gun cocks]

18:23.042 --> 18:24.750
[growls]
Also, I love you!

18:24.750 --> 18:26.000
ROOSTER: Damn it.
‐ I really do.

18:26.000 --> 18:27.667
‐ Would you just
die already!

18:27.667 --> 18:29.708
[Monkey shrieks]
[screams]

18:30.417 --> 18:33.708
‐ Okay. Goodbye forever,
my furry little friend!

18:35.792 --> 18:37.417
Augh, this isn't happening, is it?

18:37.417 --> 18:39.833
[Monkey whines]
Oh, I don't deserve peace.

18:40.583 --> 18:42.917
I'm just gonna eat shit
for the rest of eternity.

18:43.333 --> 18:45.250
Nothing ever comes easy for me.
Never has.

18:45.250 --> 18:48.542
Why would death be any different?
I mean, the whole day was pointless.

18:51.292 --> 18:54.000
And still the Monkey
says nothing.

18:54.000 --> 18:56.083
[Monkey grunts]
No, fine. Of course.

18:56.083 --> 18:59.083
No, no, no, no. Work‐work‐work
with you. That's all it is.

18:59.667 --> 19:02.458
Well, I guess the only good thing
to come out this godforsaken day

19:02.458 --> 19:04.375
is that we've now killed everyone
that's a threat

19:04.375 --> 19:06.250
in the entire city of Tokyo.

19:06.625 --> 19:09.375
So we can just stroll back
to your girlfriend's house

19:09.375 --> 19:11.875
and eat persimmons.

19:13.167 --> 19:14.208
For eternity!

19:15.542 --> 19:17.833
[dialing]

19:19.542 --> 19:21.042
‐ Hey. It's me.

19:21.833 --> 19:23.250
The Rooster is dead.

19:25.708 --> 19:27.833
MAN: [over phone]
This has gone on too long.

19:28.458 --> 19:30.125
You could not cauterize
the wound,

19:30.125 --> 19:32.667
and now this monkey
has the box.

19:33.583 --> 19:36.917
Since it's evident none of you
can handle the task at hand,

19:37.500 --> 19:39.292
I've called someone
who can.

19:40.042 --> 19:40.917
A fixer.

19:41.750 --> 19:44.625
A precise instrument.

19:44.625 --> 19:46.792
[line disconnects]

19:47.458 --> 19:49.125
‐ Who do you think he called?

19:51.167 --> 19:55.792
♪ "The Voices of Kamuy" by COMA‐CHI ♪

19:58.833 --> 20:00.958
PILOT: [over PA system]
Attention, all crew and passengers,

20:00.958 --> 20:02.792
please prepare for landing.

20:02.792 --> 20:03.708
Thank you.

20:04.375 --> 20:05.583
‐ I'm so sorry, ma'am,

20:05.583 --> 20:08.000
but we're going to need you
to put your tray table up for landing.

20:08.542 --> 20:10.375
I can help you with those bottles
if you like.

20:10.958 --> 20:12.042
[bottles clinking]

20:15.458 --> 20:20.167
♪

20:41.500 --> 20:42.708
‐ I am so sorry, ma'am,

20:43.042 --> 20:45.917
but it looks like your room
won't be ready for another hour.

20:47.542 --> 20:50.000
Please feel free to have
a complimentary drink at the bar.

20:50.958 --> 20:54.167
♪

20:54.167 --> 20:55.333
MAN:
Wow.

20:55.333 --> 20:57.625
You must really like tomatoes.

20:57.625 --> 20:59.542
Hah. Let me guess.

21:00.125 --> 21:01.208
Long day?

21:04.542 --> 21:05.875
Let me buy you another.

21:06.458 --> 21:09.583
♪

21:19.042 --> 21:21.417
♪

21:21.417 --> 21:24.042
[screaming]

21:24.042 --> 21:28.708
♪

21:33.125 --> 21:38.333
♪

21:58.917 --> 22:04.333
♪
